---
title: Crunchy Garden Wraps with Spinach Salad & Bang Bang Dressing
description: This is a ten-minute, fresh and crunchy, wrap-and-go wonder lunch! First order of business: bang bang dressing! It’s a sweet-hot combo of Sriracha, apricot jam, mayo, olive oil, and lemon—one of those sauces that’s so easy to make (and impossible to resist!) You’ll use it to dress a spinach, scallion, and cabbage slaw, then wrap it all up in a soft flour tortilla with crisp, lemony cucumber. Serve leftover bang bang salad on the side to complete a lunch idea that’s anything but garden-variety.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/648886c328c9744b12dcdc6f-97b232ba.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/648886c328c9744b12dcdc6f.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 520 kcal
  fat: 26 g
  saturated fat: 5 g
  carbohydrates: 61 g
  sugar: 18 g
  protein: 8 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 680 mg
cuisine: Chinese
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/crunchy-garden-wraps-648886c328c9744b12dcdc6f
course: main course
time required: 10 minutes
---

Wash and dry produce.

Trim @mini cucumber{1} and halve lengthwise; cut into thin wedges. Quarter @lemon{1}. Thinly slice @scallions{2}.

In a #small bowl{}, toss cucumber with juice from one lemon wedge, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @apricot jam{1}, @Sriracha{1%teaspoon}, @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, and juice from one lemon wedge. Season with salt and pepper.

Add @spinach{5%ounce}, @coleslaw mix{4%ounce}, and scallions; toss to coat.

Wrap @flour tortillas{2} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{90%seconds}.

Place tortillas on a clean work surface. Place cucumber on the bottom two-thirds of each tortilla and top with as much spinach salad as you like. Fold up bottom side of each tortilla over filling, then fold over left and right sides toward the filling. Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to form wraps.

Halve wraps on a diagonal; divide between plates and serve with any remaining spinach salad on the side.